body.name: Club Car Precedent "STAPLE ON" Golf Cart Seat Cover With Matching Rear Facing Seat Cover (2 Stripe)

byLineInfo.name: Visit the Up To Par Covers Store

features: MADE IN U.S.A - All our products are proudly made in U.S.A and are made with high quality marine grade vinyl and top stitched for extra strength and to help prevent water from getting through. All our products are made to order. We politely ask for up to 5 business days to produce and ship.
Free samples of our colors are available by request. Just let us know what colors you would like to see. The colors on your screen may differ from what you actually receive.

This seat cover is designed specifically for the model cart listed in the title and in the pictures of this listing. They are designed to fit the original unaltered seating. If your cart does not match the title or pictures, it will not fit your seating. If you do not see your cart here, we have plenty of other options in our store. Click on our logo to see more options. You may also contact us and send pictures of your cart to help verify what you may need.

DIY - Easy to Install - This is a full replacement seat cover. They are designed to be stapled on. There will be enough material to wrap under the seat and staple. Mostly all pictures you see of our products are all customer done and a lot of our customers have zero to very little experience in upholstery work.
When your cart is complete. Please help us by reviewing the product. Send us pictures of your work. We love to see our products on your cart.
body.description: What is included in this product - Staple On cover for front seat (Seat Portion). - Staple On Cover for front seat (Backrest Portion). - Staple On cover for rear seat (Seat Portion) - Satple On cover for rear seat (Backrest Portion) - Instructions will be included.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love these covers.
reviews.reviewText: I have installed two sets of these covers on an older DS and on my Precedent. The Precedent was slightly more difficult, but both carts were relatively easy. The results were very professional looking installs and really quality looking seats. Also the covers arrived much faster than expected. These covers are top shelf and look durable too. Will definitely buy them again for other carts.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 4, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality - Great looks
reviews.reviewText: These covers were perfect for my 2015 Precedent Villager 4. The original seats were worn and ugly and the cart needed a refresh. I simply followed instructions here for measurements. The installation was straight forward (it was my first effort at this). I will probably do some cleanup work on the back of the seat backs. The fabric for the seat backs could be a little longer (another inch and a half bottom to top) but what was sent worked okay.I wouldn’t hesitate to order these again if I refresh another cart!

reviews.reviewText: I received everything in less then two weeks, that is pretty awesome considering the seat covers are custom ordered. Installation took some time and patience and the fit was 100% spot on. Great product and great value for the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars REALLY spiffed up the looks of our cart
reviews.reviewText: We decided to undertake this project of recovering the seats on our Club Car Precedent that had the stock, beige seat covers. We are extremely happy with the way it turned out. We bought the set that included the standard front seat pack, plus (in our case) the back seat package that perfectly fit our MadJax 250 rear seat.They have you measure the bottom cushion in the back...and identify the kind of profile of the back of the back seat (out of 7 or 8 different profiles). What we received was PERFECT for both the front and rear seats. You can select your color combination that you would like. We contacted the seller and ordered some samples where we would know the exact colors to choose from.The quality was high and workmanship excellent.Three or four observations and/or recommendations:1) Getting the seats out when you have a rear seat installed is not particularly easy. This depends on the method the manufacturer used to mount it. It was hard for me, but very easy for a neighbor who did this same project.2) Put the vinyl cover you are working on in the clothes dryer for 5-10 minutes before you work with it. It makes it more flexible and easier to stretch.3) We bought an electric stapler - it CAN be done with a hand-operated heavy duty stapler, but this made it much easier. Amazon product https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B085XYTSM9/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_asin_title_o09_s01?ie=UTF8&psc=14) Even though you will see videos on YouTube showing a single person doing this...it's much easier with a second person - one to hold and stretch the vinyl, and one to do the stapling.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 22, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great improvement to the 2011 Club Car Golf Cart
reviews.reviewText: It took two hours with a good friend to install the covers but they were the perfect size from the company. The old seats covers were falling apart and I looked for a long time for a replacement. I was surprised that they said to leave the old covers on, but that worked out fine. As others say, it took awhile to uninstall the rear seat to measure it and put it back and then uninstall it again for the new covers. I was worried about the "G" I picked for the rear backrest but that worked great too. Just take your time and expect to put some staples in and pull them back out to get a good fit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 25, 2019
reviews.reviewText: Great product. A good economy style seat cover. DISCLAIMER: GIVE THEM THE EXAVT MEASUREMENTS OF YOUR BACKSEAT BASE CUSHION. I give an extra 2” on each side thinking “I’ll need extra slack”. This is not the case. They automatically give the extra slack so it is imperative you give the EXACT measurements. It was simply my mistake. They look great when I was done.
